            . Upon the Tryal Parsons swore, That he overtook two Men upon the Road by White-Chappel, of whom he enquired after his Sheep; that they acquainted him that they had been hired by the said Middleton to drive such a parcel of Sheep to Pancras, and from thence to Clarkenwel, where they left them in the Custody of 
